page.title: 01LANDSCAPE
page.content: We have been allocated three villages, {(Stoke Poges,Farnham Common and {Fulmer)}and their surrounding areas to survey. These villages lie only twenty miles from London. Our impression of the area as a whole is that is quite flat with some wooded parts. Is is very{built up} though it does not have a lot of shops. Pockets within the area still retain the{natural landscape}which have not been interfered with by housing planners. There is still some woodland and open spaces which have not changed for hundreds of years. The combination of open spaces,easy access to Heathrow Airport and nearby Motorways make the area attractive to{ {Commuters}.
